               Welcome to the California Early Start Home Page


   Return to Previous Page



   With Early Start . . . We can make a difference. A child with or at
   risk of developmental delay or disability can receive an "Early Start"
   in the State of California. Teams of service coordinators, healthcare
   providers, early intervention specialists, therapists, and parent
   resource specialists can evaluate and assess an infant or toddler and
   provide appropriate early intervention services to children eligible
   for California Early Start.

      What is Early Start?
          Answers to questions about which children are served, who
          provides services, how much does it cost.

      Parents' Rights
          Information for parents.

      Federal and State Statutes and Regulations
          Information about and links to the federal and state statutes
          and regulations that govern Early Start and Early Intervention
          Services.

      Complaints, Mediation, and Due Process Hearings
          (For Children From Birth to Age 3)
          Information regarding dispute resolution processes.

      Family Resource Centers/Networks
          Families can receive parent-to-parent support, Conference
          information.

      Early Start Resource Materials
          Early Start Central Directory, Publications, and link to Early
          Start Resources.

      Training and Technical Assistance
          Personnel Development, Early Start Statewide Institutes, Link to
          WestEd Center for Prevention and Early Intervention.

      Interagency Coordinating Council (ICC)
          Overview, Members, and Meeting Minutes.
